## Project Overview

AlgoMaster Online Judge is a multi-tenant, multi-role competitive programming platform designed for educational institutions. It supports secure sandboxed evaluation of 6 programming languages (C/C++/Java/Python/Go/JavaScript), providing a complete online programming teaching and competition experience.

**Tech Stack:**
- **Backend:** Rust (Edition 2021) with Axum framework, PostgreSQL, Redis
- **Frontend:** React 19, TypeScript 5.9, Vite 7, Tailwind CSS v4
- **Judge Worker:** Standalone Rust service with cgroups/seccomp sandboxing
- **Architecture:** Modular domain-driven design with 17 Rust crates

## Getting Started

For detailed installation and configuration instructions, please see [GETTING-STARTED.md](GETTING-STARTED.md).

### Quick Setup

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone <repository-url>
cd Online_Judge

# Start infrastructure (PostgreSQL + Redis)
docker compose up -d postgres redis

# Backend development
cd backend/api
cargo run

# Frontend development
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
